@SubSection
    @Title { Making the Application Translate User-Visible Strings }
    @Tag{making.the.application.translate.user.visible.strings}
@Begin
@LP
User-visible strings are marked as translation targets by wrapping
them in a @Func{tr()} call, for example:
tr @Index{ tr() }
qobject @RawIndex{ QObject }
qobject.tr @SubIndex{ tr() }
@LD @Code @RawVerbatim @Begin
    button = new QPushButton( "&Quit", this );
@End @RawVerbatim
qpushbutton @Index{ QPushButton }
would become
@LD @Code @RawVerbatim @Begin
    button = new QPushButton( tr("&Quit"), this);
@End @RawVerbatim
All @Class{QObject}qobject @Index{ QObject } subclasses that use the 
@Code{Q_OBJECT} macro implement the @Func{tr()} function.
qpushbutton @Index{ QPushButton }
q.object @Index{ Q_OBJECT }
@LP
Although the @Func{tr()} call is normally made directly since
it is usually called as a member function of a @Class{QObject}qobject
@Index{ QObject } subclass, in other cases an explicit class name can
be supplied, for example:
@LD @Code @RawVerbatim @Begin
    QPushButton::tr("&Quit")
@End @RawVerbatim
